re similar properties. We observe higher accretion rates onto the secondary\nstars than onto their primary star companion. The primary disk orientation is\nfound to be set by the initial angular momentum carried by turbulence.\nConclusions. Small (300 AU) massive protostellar disks as those frequently\nobserved nowadays can only be reproduced so far in the presence of (moderate)\nmagnetic fields with ambipolar diffusion, even in a turbulent medium. The\ninterplay between magnetic fields and turbulence sets the multiplicity of\nstellar clusters. A plasma beta $\\beta>1$ is a good indicator of streamers and\ndisks.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 30 May 2021 13:47:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-08-11"}
